Method Detail

getValueFrom

public java.lang.Object getValueFrom(java.lang.reflect.Field field,
                                     java.lang.Object object)
Return the value from a field. If a getter for this field is defined it tries to use the getter first. A getter is a method with the pattern FieldType getFieldName() where FieldType the type of the field and FieldName the name of the field is. If no such getter is defined, the value of the field will be returned by using reflection.

Parameters:
field - the Field that provides access to the field of the class.
object - the Object of the field.
Returns:
the value of the field.
Throws:
org.fest.reflect.exception.ReflectionError - if there was no getter method and it was an illegal access to the field through reflection.

setValueTo

public void setValueTo(java.lang.reflect.Field field,
                       java.lang.Object object,
                       java.lang.Object value)
Sets a value to a field. If a setter for this field is defined it tries to use the setter first. A setter is a method with the pattern void setFieldName(FieldType) where FieldType the type of the field and FieldName the name of the field is.

Parameters:
field - the Field that provides access to the field of the class.
object - the Object of the field.
Throws:
org.fest.reflect.exception.ReflectionError - if there was no such setter method for the field.

Invoke a method with one parameter and no return value.

Parameters:

value - the value for the parameter.
Throws:
